  <br>
(just to restate, the question is, &quot;Why is becoming PvP-enabled (PoD) on a blue server such a PERMANENT choice - and would there be any problems/abuses if there were a relatively simple way to toggle your PvP status off again?&quot;)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1. Go to the priest of discord. You will become a player killer on a blue server, thus you can PVP all you want against other players on a blue server. The SEVER [sic] LACK of Player killers on blue servers SHOWS that the majority of players do NOT want to engage in PVP. - Gemlin<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I think your conclusion is somewhat unsubstantiated here.  Many people on blue servers enjoy PvP action - but I would wager that it is the PERMANENCE of making the choice to &quot;go Red&quot; on a Blue server deters a lot of people from doing so.<br>
<br>
I personally play mainly on a Zek, and although mass PvP at a high level can get very close to greifing (long-term CCing of an entire guild is the equivalent of cock-blocking on blue servers), casual PvP action is actually quite fun.  And if I'm not mistaken, that is what Nextonex is looking for.  A simple way to temporarily dip into the PvP world without having to change servers or start an entirely new character from scratch on a Zek.  PvPing against friends is half the fun, anyway, and unless you can convince them to make toons on a Zek too, you'll never be able to run around WK or some other non-Arena zone with a dozen friends all duking it out.  (Arena zones are VERY limiting in terms of PvP strategies, and facing multiple opponents makes things a lot more interesting/fun).  <br>
<br>
On a side note: Nextonex, I liked your idea of making people in your group/raid immune to AoEs in PvP.  Would be a nice change on the Zeks, too, although I'm sure mass PvP would turn into Rain city pretty quickly.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
Edit  -  although it's not really on-point to Nextonex's question, with respect to Gemlin's concerns about people running in and dotting someone, and letting them take an exp death, or more people training and justifying it with PvP as an excuse:  currently, the majority of people (on Tallon, at least) are pretty good about PKing.  If someone is engaged with a mob, they'll wait until it is dead before attacking.  If accidental exp deaths due to PvP action do occur, most people (guilded, anyway) will arrange for a rez for the victim (90-96%).  <br>
Realistically, griefers are griefers:  changing the PvP system on blue servers won't make non-griefers into griefers.  The people that train you after a PvP change are the same ones that will train you now.  Taking actions like that will ruin their reputation pretty quickly, regardless of whatever lame excuse they try to provide.  Besides, you guys actually see GMs on your servers occasionally, so you have recourse to deal with them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarbonius>Zarbonius</A> at: 3/19/03 2:54:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seaotter42>SeaOtter42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 3:01:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=53>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blue Server PvP Thought for discussion</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I don't think people, including myself, need a major change to the system. Just some sort of motivation in terms of reward for using it.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
PvP on blue servers isnt supposed to have a reward. If any sort of reward system existed for PvP then players who don't want to PvP would miss out on content simply due to not wanting to PvP. This undermines the whole point of having non-PvP servers. If PvP was so popular, the PvP servers would rank a little higher on the population chart. As it is now, the Zeks are comparatively empty. <br>
<br>
If you dont like the existing PvP options on the blue servers, don't use them, but don't expect PvP rewards on a blue server, because it wouldnt be fair to people who have come to expect to experience *all* available game content without having to engage in PvP. <br>
