SeaOtter, I could be wrong, but aren't people who don't like PvP already missing out on the content of GM-run PvP events?  GM events can be (arguably) some of the more interesting content in the game.  I'm also not sure how adding an additional dimension (eg. increased roleplay via faction-based PvP) to the game, all of which was completely *optional* (i.e. red players can still only PK other red players) would detract from the enjoyment that non-red players would take from the game.  That's like saying adding more tradeskill items is unfair to people who don't want to tradeskill, no?<br>
<br>
The Zeks are emptier than other servers because PvP is a full-time system there, and not many people are willing to put up with the major pain in the ass that it can be at times (go start a non-twinked rogue on a PvP server, and you'll see what I mean).  But if you could bring only the best aspects of PvP from the Zeks to the blues and leave the negatives behind, why wouldn't you?  Especially if it's all optional? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarroslivinglight>ZarrosLivinglight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 3:34:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.e-cadfael.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/images/larger/70x100/70_057.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blue Server PvP Thought for discussion</span><hr size=1> Here's a twist on PvP that might be fun.<br>
<br>
Give players the ability to join existing factions in-game.  By doing so they become PvP+ to the enemies of said faction, and can PK them in return.  Meaning a shadow knight could join the Coldain faction, and would become PvP+ to anyone allied with the Kael giants as well as being able to PK them.<br>
<br>
This would be turned on by visiting an NPC in the faction's headquarters (Thurgadin in the case of the Coldain) and telling them &quot;I want to join&quot; which would incur +faction for them and -faction for their enemies (on an NPC level).  It could then be turned off by telling them &quot;I wish to quit&quot; which would incur a faction hit for that faction only (their enemies are still mad at you though.)  <br>
<br>
A limitation would be that you could only be a member of one faction at a time.  And they would have limited numbers of enemies.  One could walk up to the Indigo Brotherhood in Neriak and be able to engage in PvP conflict with those who joined the Emerald Warriors, Knights of Truth, and Guardians of the Vale.  Joining the Freeport Militia would make you PvP+ for those allied with the Knights of Truth.<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p>--------------<br>
