The thing is, EQ's faction system isn't as black and white as that. While I think this could work in some areas of the game, such as Velious, the rest of the game just doesn't support it.<br>
<br>
Imagine if factions were the PvP switch; Being KoS to a faction opened you to attacks from players that are allied with that faction. This could work, and since factions can be changed pretty easily, it would allow players to move from +PvP status to -PvP status with relative ease.<br>
Since all factions between KoS and Ally would be -PvP, it'd allow people to choose their own allys, and even cater to those that don't want to PvP ever.<br>
<br>
Rewards? Think about all the quests you have to be allied with a race in order to complete; There are tons. <br>
So, by becoming a races ally, you'd be able to do those quests and reap their rewards, but you'd be open to PvP while you were allied. Once you've finished the quest, you could drop your faction back to Warmly, and you'd no longer be +PvP.<br>
<br>
The problem is there is a large portion of the games factions which are impossible to raise (like Goblin faction in Kunark, or Ring of Scale faction), and many factions don't have a opposite (Dwarves Vs Frost Giants, Dragons Vs Storm Giants). In order for a system like this to work, it'd require a serious overhaul of how the current faction system works. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1163<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 5:36:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25419.topic&index=57>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blue Server PvP Thought for discussion</span><hr size=1> Before Gem can respond yet another time with his macro, in case anyone is still unsure, pvp is implemented on blue servers.  <br>
